^b@2^*BMarty Bergen: ^*N|cp||at|We love hands where our key suits split well. We find it very annoying when we get a bad split in a key suit. That is especially true in trump when sometimes a bad split is fatal. But you want to try to survive bad splits and make the most of good splits.|
PG| ***** 1 ***** |


cp|8|AT|

^b@2^*BMarty Bergen: ^*N|cp||at|The following is worth keeping in mind on all hands. When things look bad, whether because of bad luck or bad bidding, think optimistically. 'What if?' Give yourself a chance. On the other hand, when you are in a contract that looks cold, play devil's advocate. You need to be pessimistic and concern yourself with things going wrong, such as bad splits. Figure out if there is a way that you can survive bad luck rather than complaining about it later on. Certainly subjects such as safety plays should be part of your arsenal.|
PG| ***** 2 ***** |


